	systems is addressed. Interference aware allocation of time-frequency
	slots is accomplished by letting receivers transmit a busy burst
	(BB) in a time-multiplexed minislot, upon successful reception of
	data. Exploiting TDD channel reciprocity, an exclusion region around
	a victim receiver is established, whose size is determined by a threshold
	parameter, known at the entire network. By adjusting this threshold
	parameter, the amount of cochannel interference (CCI) caused to active
	receivers in neighbouring cells is dynamically controlled. It is
	demonstrated that by tuning the interference threshold parameter,
